      • nameToSId

        public static java.lang.String nameToSId(java.lang.String name,
                                         SBMLDocument doc)
        Generates a valid SId from a given name. If the name already is a valid SId, the name is returned. If the SId already exists in this document, "_<number>" will be appended and the next free number is being assigned. => See SBML L2V4 document for the Definition of SId. (Page 12/13)
        Parameters:
        name -
        Returns:
        SId
